20 April 2016Minister of Communications Ms Faith Muthambi is set to deliver keynote address at the 2nd EThekwini Social Cohesion Conference on the 21st of April 2016, Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban. EThekwini Municipality was first city to host social cohesion dialogue back in 2013, this culminated in a National Dialogue hosted by the Minister of Arts &amp; Culture in Kliptown. It is in the South African historical context that Social Cohesion and Nation Building has become a political imperative. Minister Muthambi will engages conference as a keynote speaker on the topic SA Media: The cornerstone of Nation Building or a perpetrator of our racial past The media has role to play in nation building, promoting social cohesion and creating awareness about human rights . Said Muthambi Session is scheduled as follows: Venue: Moses Mabhida Stadium. Date: 21 April 2016 Time: 13h30 16h30.Enquiries: Mish Molakeng Contact: 082 469 3997 Issued by GCIS on behalf of the Ministry of Communications